This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the segmentation of brain anatomy from MRI images. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNN) also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of forward models to augment the training data suggests that it may belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of multi-center initiatives and protocol harmonization suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
